will do this again this year. <a href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/help-with-swerve-curve/439835/7">Here</a> is a comment I wrote last summer about our heading/drift correction logic; in addition to using it for heading correction, we also use it for snapping to an angle based on the D-pad. The TL;DR:</p>
<ul>
<li>Use a <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> controller to rotate the robot to a <code>desiredHeading</code> variable whenever the driver isn’t manually rotating the robot (you don’t want this to interfere with manual control).</li>
<li>For drift correction, set that heading when the driver is manually rotating (as that is the intended heading)</li>
<li>For snapping to an angle, just set that variable manually; it’ll use that <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> controller to rotate itself to that angle.</li>
</ul>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":20,"updated_at":"2024-02-10T18:50:44.637Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":14,"reads":442,"readers_count":441,"score":198.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":454211,"topic_slug":"snap-to-heading","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/help-with-swerve-curve/439835/7","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Help with "Swerve Curve"","clicks":58}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":53201,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"8096A"},"post_url":"/t/snap-to-heading/454211/2","custom_user_title":"8096A","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3306579,"name":"","username":"four","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/four/{size}/199902_2.png","created_at":"2024-02-10T21:34:52.018Z","cooked":"<p>I think your <code>convertCardinalDirections()</code> is what I needed. Does <a href="https://github.com/Delmar-Robotics-Engineers-At-MADE/2024-Robot/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/robot/Commands/Drivetrain/RapidHeading.java">this</a> look like it would work?</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":20,"updated_at":"2024-02-10T21:34:52.018Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":385