ete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":53201,"username":"tails618","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/tails618/{size}/188357_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":60512,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Doubling the current limit does not make it work."},"post_url":"/t/snap-to-heading/454211/5","custom_user_title":"Doubling the current limit does not make it work.","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3307025,"name":"","username":"tails618","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/tails618/{size}/188357_2.png","created_at":"2024-02-11T15:54:20.544Z","cooked":"<p>Looks like this should work. The main thing I noticed is that the <code>RapidHeading</code> command only runs when the POV isn’t in the center, so I think you will have to hold it down until you’ve snapped to the angle, but I might be wrong.</p>
<p>Your <code>isFinished</code> function also always returns false; I don’t know whether that will cause any issues. You might be able to modify that to make it so it finishes once you’ve snapped to the angle, which would probably fix the above issue.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":20,"updated_at":"2024-02-11T15:54:20.544Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":286,"readers_count":285,"score":62.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":454211,"topic_slug":"snap-to-heading","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":60512,"username":"four","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/four/{size}/199902_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":53201,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"8096A"},"post_url":"/t/snap-to-heading/454211/6","custom_user_title":"8096A","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3307074,"name":"Adam","username":"lol","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/l/5daacb/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-02-11T17:44:38.939Z","cooked":"<p>What values do you use for your heading controller?</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":20,"updated_at":"2024-02-11T17:44:38.939Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":235,"readers_count":234,"score":52.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":454211,"topic_slug":"snap-to-heading","display_username":"Adam","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":53201,"username":"tails618","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/tails618/{size}/188357_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":56055,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/snap-to-heading/454211/7","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3307106,"name":"","username":"four","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/four/{size}/199902_2.png","created_at":"2024-02-11T18:21:02.006Z","cooked":"<p>That behavior is intentional. The drivers want to use a flight stick, but this always leads to driving like a tank because it is difficult to rotate in a controlled way while moving. I am trying to use this as a sort of work-around so that a direction can be held while driving which is why <code>isFinished</code> returns false.</p>
<p>Is there an advantage to binding the trigger as <code>onFalse</code> rather than <code>whileFalse</code>? It seems that this should be an actively commanded thing that can be released immediately.</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":20,"updated_at":"2024-02-11T18:21:02.006Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":224,"readers_count":223,"score":49.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":454211,"topic_slug":"snap-to-heading","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":53201,"username":"tails618","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/tails618/{size}/188357_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":60512,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Doubling the current limit does not make it work."},"post_url":"/t/snap-to-heading/454211/8","custom_user_title":"Doubling the current limit does not make it work.","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3307120,"name":"Eric (319)","username":"EKM_319","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/ekm_319/{size}/230932_2.png","created_at":"2024-02-11T18:30:02.454Z","cooked":"<p>See we’re working on a Snap to heading function now. What i’m curious about is how teams in the past have handled rotation2d rollover at 180/-180 degrees.</p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":20,"updated_at":"2024-02-11T18:30:02.454Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":214,"readers_count":213,"score":52.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":454211,"topic_slug":"snap-to-heading","display_username":"Eric (319)","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":23786,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Awaiting our Robot Overlords since 2013"},"post_url":"/t/snap-to-heading/454211/9","custom_user_title":"Awaiting our Robot Overlords since 2013","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3307132,"name":"Nathan Fletcher","username":"NatFletch","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/natfletch/{size}/211725_2.png","created_at":"2024-02-11T18:40:05.406Z","cooked":"<p>Convert your joystick inputs to polar coordinates and do some simple math. Team 1806 does it like this:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public double snapRotation(){
        DoubleSupplier x = () -&gt; -driverController.getRightX();
        DoubleSupplier y = () -&gt; -driverController.getRightY();

        double[] rightJoyPolarCoordinate = PolarCoordinate.toPolarCoordinate(y,x);

        double r = rightJoyPolarCoordinate[0];
        double theta = Units.radiansToDegrees(rightJoyPolarCoordinate[1]);

        if(r &lt;0.8){
            return RobotContainer.S_SWERVE.getSwerveDrive().getOdometryHeading().getDegrees();
        }

        theta /= 45;
        theta = Math.round(theta) * 45;
        return theta;
    }
</code></pre>
<p>Dividing by 45 degrees then rounding the answer then multiplying back by 45 degrees ensures that your only values will be 0,45,90,135,180,-135,-90,-45<br>
Full repo is here if you want our PolarCoordinates class: <a href="https://github.com/frc1806/Crescendo-1806" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">GitHub - frc1806/Crescendo-1806: FRC Team 1806's 2024 Robot Code</a></p>
